DISCLAIMER:

This software is designed for educational purposes as part of the "Desarrollo 
de Software Seguro" course at Universidad de las Fuerzas Armadas ESPE.

The vulnerability detection capabilities are based on publicly available data
from CVE, NVD, and GitHub Advisory databases. The predictions and alerts 
generated by the machine learning models should be used as guidance and 
complementary to manual security reviews and established security practices.

The authors and contributors are not responsible for:
- False positives or false negatives in vulnerability detection
- Any security breaches or damages resulting from the use of this software
- Misuse or misinterpretation of the generated reports and predictions

Users are encouraged to:
- Verify all findings with security experts
- Follow industry-standard security practices
- Keep the system updated with the latest vulnerability data
- Use this tool as part of a comprehensive security strategy

For production use, additional validation, testing, and security auditing
are strongly recommended.
